Citation.sTitle: Enthalpies of Mixing of Liquid In-Sn and In-Sn-Zn Alloys
Citation.sAbstract: Partial and integral enthalpies of mixing of liquid ternary In-Sn-Zn alloys were determined at  500deg C along seven sections over a large composition range. Additionally, binary alloys of the  constituent system In-Sn were investigated at the same temperature. The measurements were carried  out using a Calvet-type microcalorimeter and a drop calorimetric technique. The binary data were  evaluated by means of a standard Redlich-Kister polynomial fit whereas ternary data were fitted on the  basis of an extended Redlich-Kister-Muggianu model for substitutional solutions.
